RECOVER
        orphan file record to file

        -i info about file (default)
        -r recover

        -s work in sectors
        -c work in clusters

        -C cluster size bytes

        -o offset of file record
        -O offset of start of volume

        Use $Boot at offset x option
        or decode $Boot at offset x

        search for NTFS metadata option

        can intuit clustersize from 0x30 attribute

        create a sparse file if some dataruns are missing

